Source: nexigon-debian
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Silitics GmbH <info@silitics.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://nexigon.dev/
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/nexigon/nexigon
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/nexigon/nexigon.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: nexigon-agent-gnu
Architecture: any
Conflicts: nexigon-agent-musl
Description: Nexigon device agent (glibc build)
 Nexigon is a remote device management platform. The agent runs on
 managed devices and connects them to a Nexigon Hub for fleet
 management, deployment, and remote access. This package provides
 nexigon-agent linked against glibc.
 .
 This source package is metadata-only; see /usr/share/doc/nexigon-agent-gnu
 and the upstream repository for the buildable source.

Package: nexigon-agent-musl
Architecture: any
Conflicts: nexigon-agent-gnu
Description: Nexigon device agent (musl build)
 Nexigon is a remote device management platform. The agent runs on
 managed devices and connects them to a Nexigon Hub for fleet
 management, deployment, and remote access. This package provides
 nexigon-agent statically linked against musl libc.
 .
 This source package is metadata-only; see /usr/share/doc/nexigon-agent-musl
 and the upstream repository for the buildable source.

Package: nexigon-cli-gnu
Architecture: any
Conflicts: nexigon-cli-musl
Description: Nexigon command-line interface (glibc build)
 Nexigon is a remote device management platform. The CLI is used to
 administer Nexigon Hubs, manage repositories, and orchestrate device
 fleets from a workstation or CI environment. This package provides
 nexigon-cli linked against glibc.
 .
 This source package is metadata-only; see /usr/share/doc/nexigon-cli-gnu
 and the upstream repository for the buildable source.

